OUD estimates for the NYS counties ## Figure 2

## Figure 3 Counties trends ## Figure 4 Using this Figure, we would like to show how under-diagnosed OUD were accounted for in our OUD estimate. We hypothesize that high overdose deaths are due to high untreated OUD. ##Figure 5 The percentage under-diagnosed based on our estimate is plotted against income.

#Supplement ## Figure S1 In a county without a severe issue of under-diagnosis OR a fast-growing OUD epidemic (faster than the treatment effort), we expect the drop of overdose fatality as a response to increase in treatment effort (such as what we found in these counties below).

## Figure S2 The following counties show another trend: growing overdose fatality, despite increases in treatment effort. This suggests 1) treatment is not keeping pace with the OUD epidemic in the county; 2) under-diagnosis. Both could be happening at the same time. ##Figure S3 Undiagnosed OUD is not distributed evenly across demographic groups.
